g.text: The idea is having an multi-agent chain at the moment, might evolve later on
to further enhance results if needed.
To make the architecture "interesting" we're using the ReAct framework for single agents and replacing its nodes with proper agents.
The main idea is trying to user the different agents personas and "independentness" to yield better results, overcoming ReAct's current limitations.
i.e. An independent agent checking the answer might be more effective at its job than a node of a ReAct agent.
Calling it "Neo ReAct" also sounds cool
